<item>
            <title>[SWF-409] Custom scoped actions are cannot be instantiated</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-409</link>
                <project id="10050" key="SWF">Spring Web Flow</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If an action is marked as scope=&quot;flow&quot; there is an error when it is accessed by the flow execution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org.springframework.webflow.engine.builder.FlowArtifactLookupException: Unable to obtain a Action flow artifact with id &apos;testController&apos;: make sure there is a valid &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;interface org.springframework.webflow.execution.Action&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; exported with this id; nested exception is org.springframework.beans.factory.BeanCreationException: Error creating bean with name &apos;testController&apos;: Scope &apos;flow&apos; is not active for the current thread; consider defining a scoped proxy for this bean if you intend to refer to it from a singleton; nested exception is java.lang.IllegalStateException: No flow execution context is bound to this thread&lt;br/&gt;
	org.springframework.webflow.engine.builder.xml.LocalFlowServiceLocator.getBean(LocalFlowServiceLocator.java:221)&lt;br/&gt;
	org.springframework.webflow.engine.builder.xml.LocalFlowServiceLocator.getAction(LocalFlowServiceLocator.java:124)&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P.S. I am using JSF (so no FlowExecutor).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
